I someone see this journal becoming one big rant....I think I need that outlet.

I miss my "coonass" friends and sitting on campus, starting the "pit" at 7 in the morning while keeping an eye on our Port-A-Potty just in case a stranger decides they want to use it without our permission (dammit we paid for it there will be no stranger stuff in there), and awaiting parades were beads will come down like rain. I always knew that a day would come when I would have to say goodbye to someone so special in my life.  And while that day has not come yet, a certain turn of events has made me realize that it could come soon.  I found out last night that my grandmother who basically help raise me is in the hospital with pneumonia.  What makes it worse is that she has had Alzheimer's for about 8 years or so.  In that time I always hoped that it was just a phase and that my grandmother who always had ice cream with Hershey's chocolate syrup waiting for me when I got off the bus from school or the woman who let me pick out as much junk food as I wanted at the grocery store during the summer (much to the discontent of my mother) would never leave me and would remember me again.  I always imagined that I would bring my children to visit her and she would be at my wedding, but she wasn't able to come to my wedding and I now I have to come to understand that she will probably never see my children.  What makes it harder is I never knew my grandfather (her husband) because he died when my mom was really young, so that whole part of my family will be gone.  I often cry because I never knew my grandfather and wish I knew more about him.  My mom doesn't talk about it because she either doesn't remember much or it hurts her to do so.

But what makes it absolutely life shattering is the fact that I haven't seen her in 3 years.  How could I let myself choose to be so selfish and not try to visit the woman that taught me so much and always thought I was a perfect angel no matter what I did?  Instead I let my fear of breaking down when I saw her and getting upset that she wouldn't remember and that she was no in a nursing home that I absolutely hated (because the one she was in previously shut down) get in the way.  And no matter how much my mom tells me that she wouldn't want any of the grandchildren or her children for that matter to see her the way she is I still will always feel guilty.  From what I hear she doesn't talk much and just sits there with a blank stare, not at all like the woman I new that always had a smile on her face and carried herself with such grace and dignity.  She had everything to be proud of, she raised five children by herself and they all turned out to be wonderful, but she has no memory of that.  

It breaks my heart to know that I'll get a phone call one day saying I need to come back to Louisiana because my "Maw Maw T" left us.  I'm having a hard time keeping myself together knowing that she is  in the hospital I just don't know what it will do to me to know that is so much worse.

So for those of you who pray, please keep my grandmother in your prayers and for those of you who don't pray please keep her in your thoughts.

... so I contacted our human resources girl to find out if I was in fact going to be able to transfer to our Roanoke billing office.

Here is a little background since I just realized I may not have posted the whole story:

My husband was offered a position (the same as he has now) in Roanoke (Virginia for those of you who forgot I live here now) in July right before we left to go to Louisiana for a couple of weeks.  He gladly accepted (anything to get us out of boring as all get out Martinsville).  While I was excited about moving to a "real" city, I was also worried about my job situation, taking in to account that I had JUST gotten insurance in June (thus taking me off of Carl's extremely expensive insurance) and a raise, and I was getting promoted when I got back from Louisiana.  But wait!  maybe there was a way to keep it all!  You see the company I work for has offices all over Virginia, West Virginia, North Carolina, and other states in the area, and even better their main office is in Salem (next door neighboors with Roanoke for the geographically challenged) and a billing office in Roanoke.  So maybe I thought, just maybe I could transfer if there was a job opening.  When I got back from Louisiana I had to tell my boss that we may want to hold off on that promotion because I was leaving the office by the end of the month and moving to Roanoke because of my husband's transfer.  While she was upset (hey I guess so she has asked more than once if I could be cloned!  so i expected her to be shocked and upset) but was more than open to the idea of getting the corporate office to transfer me when I asked if it would be possible.  She made a phone call to human resources, human resources made a phone call to the Roanoke billing office, and boom yes there was indeed an opening at the Roanoke office doing what my promotion would have had me doing.  So Tuesday I had an informal interview (over the phone so i wouldn't have to miss work of course) with the manager at the Roanoke office.  In her exact words "I have no problem with you tranfering here, I'll let human resources know and she should contact you soon."

Ok so today comes and almost goes and I still haven't heard anything.  Now keep in mind the cost of living in Roanoke is WAY different than that in Martinsville so me having to find a job would need to start happening like NOW so I would possibly have a job once we moved there, because having only one source of income is not an option at the moment.  So as said above I contacted human resources to see what was going on reminding them that the move would be soon so I need to know something like now.  I was so scared that she was going to say "well we reconsidered and even though the account manager liked you we just don't think it will be possible at this time."  But she said "I just finished talking to the account manager and the position is yours if you want it!"


WOOO HOOOO!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  No more stressing out about having to live like a homeless person for a month or so until I found a job.  And get this it comes with another raise since it is considered a promotion!!!  And even though I used all my vacation time when I went to Louisiana I will get a couple of days off (paid) to move.  I love the company I work for!

I guess you could say I was just tired to celebrating without him, and it was even worse this year because I don't have friends with me in Virginia to make up for him not being here.

Ok anways...about 10am I get a dozen roses from him delivered to my office. So long story short I had a wonderful birthday, even if I did spend it at work and Boy Scout camp.

Ok that is enough of an update for now.  I need to finish cleaning the apartment and do laundry.

Well my husband left yesterday to spend three months running a summer Boy Scout camp.  It is about two hours away from here so he will be coming home every Wednesday (a new requirement by his boss because he still needs to do things for his district during the summer too) and probably a couple of Saturdays a month.  While I don't like the drive up there (once you get off the interstate it is LITTLE country mountain roads) I will try to go at least once a month on a Saturday.  Of course because he left yesterday it stormed like all hell had broke loose.  At least it only lasted for about 20 minutes.  Thankfully my husband took his friend that has been staying with us for the last week with him.  I thought MAYBE just MAYBE he had matured but I was soooo wrong.  He hasn't matured one bit, he is loud and has no volume control (and we live in a VERY quiet complex, which is the way I like it), and likes to argue just because.  And he is VERY ignorant so his fights are always pointless and end up with me going "OK WHATEVER! Think what you want even if it is wrong" and leaving the room because I can't stand ignorance.  I respect everyone's opinion but when you don't respect mine back and try to get me to change my opinion because it isn't your opinion then thats when we have problems.  THANK GOD HE IS GONE! 

In other news when I go back home (Louisiana) for two weeks in July for the weddings I am in we won't have to leave our cats at the vet for boarding.  Which means an extra 150 dollars in our pocket that we can get a rental car with and I won't have the guilt (and lots of crying that goes with that) knowing my cats are stuck in a cage all day for two weeks.  I am lucky enough to work with wonderful caring people and one of them loves cats and is always at our apartment complex feeding her friend's cat when she goes away for the weekend so she volunteered to feed ours while we are gone.  I am going to have to get her something really nice as a thank you for doing this for us.

Well that is about it.  Hope everyone is doing super terrific!

Once again my husband went out of town this weekend and won't be home for about another 4 hours.  Thankfully this was one of the rare times that we didn't have severe weather that made me freak out and feel like a two year old in a dark room.  I am really starting to hate that he is always gone.  Even during the week he has meetings almost every night.  Then to make it worse he will be gone from the second week of June until the beginning of August.  Which means this will be the THIRD year in a row that he isn't hear to celebrate my birthday.  At least years previously my friends were around to help me celebrate but not this time.  The rate of divorce for his profession is high and I am beginning to understand why.  Not that I am anywhere near wanting a divorce, I am just irritated with his job demands.  It's like his bosses and people that volunteer for him have no respect for the fact that he has a wife at home.  They are CONSTANTLY calling at all hours of the night and day to talk to him.  I made him send out an e-mail to all of his volunteers last week that said "Now that my office phone has been transfered to my apartment, if any phone calls are received after 9:00pm, on weekends (especially Sundays), or on holidays the phone will be handed to my wife and you can explain to her why you are calling on said time/day.  I guarentee no excuse you give her will be good enough for her to give the phone to me or prevent you from being fussed at."  Now I don't think my demands are asking too much.  I mean do they not have families ????  Do they also get neglected as much as I do because they absolutely must talk to my husband at 10 at night???  UGH!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Ok that felt good to get out.  

Hope everyone is having a better day than I am.

I am taking a break from doing my Louisiana taxes.  All those numbers make my head hurt.  And the fact that I know we are going to have to pay them sucks even more.  I already did it on Turbo Tax just to make sure my numbers come out similar to theirs.  Anyways... Not much has been going on around here just work, sleep, and demon cats.  Oh except for today when I went to Wal-Mart.  I now know because of my experience I will never go to Wal-Mart without my husband or go in the middle of the night when no high school kids can attack me.  

So there is the Wal-Mart story:


First of all I hate going to Wal-Mart so I was not in a good mood and I just had got stuck behind some little girl who was paying for her beef jerky stick with pennies!  So yeah I wasn't happy.  I walk outside take off to my car (about a mile out because of all the people) at a near sprint because I am going downhill with a heavy basket and I just want to get the hell out of there.  I hear "hey!" so I turn around and this guy is running after me and asking me to hold up and so I ask him for what?  And he proceeds to tell me he has to do something for a communications class to get over his fear of public speaking and raise money to go to Europe at the same time.  Ok yeah whatever.  So he starts asking me questions and just to amuse him I answer.  Of course it comes up that I am married so I think he will get the hint that # 1 I am not available and # 2 I am probably to old for him (even though it is commonplace around here to get married young and I look like I am 16). But yet as he is giving me his whole "buy a magazine and help me go to Europe" spill he tries flirting with me.  So of course being the bitch I am I let him talk and then when he is finished filling out a form with fake info that I gave him thinking he is going to sell me a two year subscription to Stuff magazine for 48 dollars.  I stop him and say "Look maybe yall are really going to Europe and that is great and maybe you are doing a communication class project which is even better but here is my problem.  First of all you tell me you go to a high school in Roanoke which is an hour away and a city I would probably pull out of my ass because it is the only big city near here besides Greensboro.  Second of all 48 dollars for a two year subscription? I can get that cheaper through the magazine company itself. So you aren't giving me a deal.  Thirdly I told you I was married and very happily married and yet you still flirted with me as if I was your high school girlfriend.  I am 22 years old and married so you totally don't have a shot in hell and it didn't help you sell magazines.  And if this is really for a communications class you would have failed.  Because you see you have picked the wrong person to tell that to.  I competed in public speaking at state and national levels in high school and won at all of them. So I suggest you practice a little more, slow down when you talk, speak clearly, maintain eye contact, and flirting wont' sell to a anyone older than you who is married." And what is his reply? "So I guess you don't want a magazine" The only thing I could do is walk away laughing hysterically.  I mean he even tried lines like "so how do you spell your name is G-O-R-G-E-O-U-S?" and something about are you greek? and I tuned out the rest. Where do kids get this stuff?  So I really hope they try calling the police department (which is what he thinks my telephone number is) and get them to buy a subscription.

Ok I feel better now.  Stupid little boys!
